pageContext.claim: “When he said that really what he was focused on was trying to be number one in his class at Yale, to me that was so believable. I understand college very well, and I understand being number one in your class, and I understand a lot of things.”
pageContext.analysis: Supreme Court nominee Brett Kavanaugh was not number one at Yale; he graduated cum laude or in the top 30 percent. Trump suggests he was number one at the Wharton School at the University of Pennsylvania but he was not.
